This is similar to scala/bug#3078 but the code that triggers the bug is different. If the class is not a case class then the test gets launched without any problems. BTW it doesn't make any difference if the case class is top level or inside another class/object.

Tested with r20979
```scala
class CaseClassAstErrorTest {

  @org.junit.Test
  def test_method() {
    assert(true)
  }
  
}
case class AnInt(i: Int)
```
```scala
